The paper focuses on exploring the inner workings and fine-grained results of neural re-ranking models in Information Retrieval systems. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Natural Language Processing (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Computer Vision (cs.CV). However, since the paper specifically deals with Information Retrieval and neural re-ranking models, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category.
